For this¬†fourth and¬†final¬†article of our¬†little series¬†on single-element loaders, we are going to explore 3D patterns. When creating a 3D element, it‚Äôs hard to imagine that¬†just¬†one¬†HTML¬†element¬†is¬†enough to simulate¬†something like all¬†six¬†faces of a cube. But ¬†maybe we can get away with something more cube-like¬†instead by showing only the front three sides of the shape ‚Äî it‚Äôs totally possible and that‚Äôs what we‚Äôre going to do together.








